article.description: Nicholls rolls by SE Louisiana 71-64 in Southland
article.headline: Nicholls rolls by SE Louisiana 71-64 in Southland
article.linkText: Nicholls rolls by SE Louisiana 71-64 in Southland
article.story: KATY, Texas -- Dantrell Thomas scored 27 points and had six assists as fifth-seeded Nicholls State beat its rival Southeastern Louisiana 71-64 in the first round of the Southland Conference tournament on Wednesday. Nicholls won its first conference tournament game since 2009 and will face No. 4 seed Northwestern State on Thursday. Thomas, averaging 15.7 points, made 7 of 12 field goals and 11 free throws for Nicholls State (14-14). T.J. Carpenter had 13 points and Liam Thomas grabbed 12 rebounds. Dantrell Thomas scored six points during an 8-0 Nicholls State run to push a one-point lead to 60-51 with 3:44 left. Jeffery Ricard scored six consecutive SE Louisiana points to get within 62-58, but the Lions would get no closer. Dantrell Thomas made four free throws in the final 30 seconds. Dre Evans scored 15 points for No. 8 seed SE Louisiana (12-18), while Antonnio Benton had 12 and nine rebounds.
